comments: Bullock (NYK) extends his arm out as he runs by Tatum (BOS) and marginal contact occurs that does not affect Tatum's ability to maintain control of the ball.
Bullock (NYK) cleanly deflects the pass away from Smart (BOS) and any body contact as they both reach for the loose ball is deemed incidental.
During the rebound, Thompson (BOS) makes incidental contact with Barrett (NYK).
Gibson (NYK) could be deemed to be imminently exiting the lane within three seconds.

Barrett (NYK) saves the ball before it goes out of bounds and Williams (BOS) cleanly deflects the errant pass away from Gibson (NYK). Any contact between WIlliams and Gibson as they pursue the loose ball is deemed marginal.
Randle (NYK) slightly turns his body and marginal contact occurs as he contests Brown's (BOS) driving shot attempt.

Williams (BOS) maintains a legal guarding position and absorbs the contact from Randle (NYK) during the drive. Randle temporarily loses control of the ball as he tries to gather by cradling the ball against his body.
Tatum (BOS) establishes himself in a screening position in Payton's (NYK) path and absorbs the contact.
Tatum (BOS) comes to a stop and slightly extends his arm to disengage from Payton (NYK) when marginal contact occurs.
Randle (NYK) establishes himself in a screening position in Langford's (BOS) path and absorbs the contact.
Smart (BOS) slips and falls as he runs to the perimeter to close out on Burks (NYK).
Burks (NYK) commits a take foul on Brown (BOS).
Brown (BOS) maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt by Burks (NYK) and cleanly blocks the shot.
Burks (NYK) commits a take foul on Smart (BOS).
Langford (BOS) legally contests Payton's (NYK) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Payton (NYK) commits a take foul on Tatum (BOS).
Langford (BOS) commits a take foul on Barrett (NYK).
